<body>
    <h1>Check Occupancy</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"9678bd3beb79"><strong>Component type:</strong> Actio=
n</p>
<p local-id=3D"e9101b8e3baf"><strong>Category:</strong> Spaces, Rates &amp;=
 Occupancy</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"bdbfa81960da" id=3D"CheckOccupancy-Overview">Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"04a65139286e">The <strong>Check Occupancy</strong> action ca=
lculates the occupancy percentage for your property on a specific date and =
compares it against a threshold you define. Based on the result, the workfl=
ow continues through one of two output ports =E2=80=94 <strong>Above Thresh=
old</strong> or <strong>Below Threshold</strong> =E2=80=94 allowing you to =
build conditional logic into your automations.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b5e2485e0e1d">This is useful for scenarios where you want to=
 trigger different actions depending on how busy the property is. For examp=
le, you could automatically adjust pricing, send promotional offers when oc=
cupancy is low, or notify managers when occupancy is high.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"8df5e997-1c14-4abd-9328-62ab4861539d">
<h2 local-id=3D"7d014b12b0c9" id=3D"CheckOccupancy-InputFields">Input Field=
s</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"c8f7f8b2-763b-46d0-8637-b2c=
d5805432f" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"40b5882c-07c2-48c2-82e9-c670e8588d61">
<th data-local-id=3D"17f59042-bc4b-48f1-a371-32579c78ec48" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"305497730d11">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"ebfaa8cf-2d94-4e1c-86a8-5c0e2246b64f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2b2921fb488c">Required</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"26007e85-c461-40b7-a0cd-454656524614" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"499a24e34e41">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"f0b9023a-3b7b-4912-822c-03eadfcf4c95" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"34b39995b9ed">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"7093ed31-8c64-4b16-a02a-142fdb596895">
<td data-local-id=3D"f9c342e2-1e73-4fcb-b98b-71963603de19" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e2a5a90f4a7d"><strong>Date</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"911e0050-be49-4a0a-9463-b9c3636c7fae" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"01212216d6ab"><strong>Required</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"aa4275fd-cb57-4312-90fa-4338b8715e6c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3d31347695cc">Date</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fd17cd79-ba0d-4f19-a4ed-3e30e984a69f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7479b5c8594d">The date to check occupancy for. The format is=
 <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code>. Only the date portion is used; time is ignored. O=
ccupancy is calculated for the full day (from the start of the specified da=
te to the start of the next day).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c64b85e4-7fe3-4a16-891f-459fb77ecb47">
<td data-local-id=3D"07c5ad05-068a-47c1-980c-1204c78bcb71" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3df268e586bf"><strong>Occupancy Percentage Threshold</strong=
></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7cb5286b-f593-48d0-9680-2ea4ae8c9399" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"43c68c406eea"><strong>Required</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c031573f-30bb-430e-9d4c-85eae74b1d53" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6cd9e507f3d8">Number</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"bc179337-3ecd-4273-9877-42d81dc96ae0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ab29fdc7f6d2">The occupancy percentage to compare against, e=
xpressed as a value between <code>0</code> and <code>100</code>. For exampl=
e, entering <code>80</code> means 80%. The calculated occupancy is compared=
 to this threshold to determine which output port the workflow continues th=
rough.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"baf9f1f6-f1fb-4730-afd8-bbcb04df799f">
<td data-local-id=3D"cf84f9c7-f75d-4c1e-a51f-d7baddcab299" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6b719b331c0c"><strong>Bookable Services</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"560974ce-0fef-4d7a-a4cb-2817597ac9e3" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b283eb616477"><strong>Optional</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ca811eb7-eba5-43f9-89e2-77f917dd0fc7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"58ef07678f55">Multi-select dropdown</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"56b5b81a-3dc7-4ba6-bb2b-5be400783930" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"46a21dc12f4d">Select one or more bookable services to narrow=
 the occupancy calculation to specific services (e.g., only the "Stay" serv=
ice). If no services are selected, all bookable services in the property ar=
e included in the calculation.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"cf4f4335-c60e-4148-877a-4f4e14e78008">
<h2 local-id=3D"dd9164206766" id=3D"CheckOccupancy-OutputPorts">Output Port=
s</h2>
<p local-id=3D"b851f2db5c34">This component has two output ports. Only one =
is activated per execution, depending on whether the calculated occupancy i=
s above or below the specified threshold. This allows you to branch your wo=
rkflow into different paths.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"2ded9d9dbe2a" id=3D"CheckOccupancy-AboveThreshold">Above Th=
reshold</h3>
<p local-id=3D"40d76a40b92f">Activated when the calculated occupancy percen=
tage is <strong>equal to or greater than</strong> the specified threshold.<=
/p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"e5f81b7d-c26e-47aa-a512-5cd=
95014800b" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"346dbd1d-fa51-454a-a2fb-fad3d2c161c2">
<th data-local-id=3D"1a2b14c6-c87d-4594-873b-924ed938e73d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"210d04d5c016">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"86553ec1-a6f3-425a-8c26-5eb1417827ab" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"77ac9c5b2528">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"764f23d4-352d-4a11-a878-db9adeaa798b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"6db5b23eb510">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"23d16026-d688-4e69-a5a9-4345b64bccdc">
<td data-local-id=3D"d691b6b2-f9d6-4f01-bfd0-f0255a056d0d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d266d6ef0a50"><strong>Above Threshold</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b8158e7b-2863-4e08-a1dd-3140068ce829" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6ac59809028c">Boolean</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e32a332f-0707-4867-befd-f167498e53ed" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"49f41fd70b33">Always <code>true</code> on this port. Indicat=
es that the occupancy met or exceeded the threshold.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"1e85636ab930" id=3D"CheckOccupancy-BelowThreshold">Below Th=
reshold</h3>
<p local-id=3D"61f007796267">Activated when the calculated occupancy percen=
tage is <strong>strictly less than</strong> the specified threshold.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"bcb4615b-59e1-4c95-b9db-488=
561a87745" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"1e896bd7-747d-42f2-9fc2-7732716b0ddf">
<th data-local-id=3D"f559fa6f-0620-41f2-9a6b-1e688ca6645a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"b91d1b863d10">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"afe39de5-8a2d-4c63-99f5-ff27b7ad199d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"f11cdc1ba9b9">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"5a16ac20-4fd0-4b23-a1c5-3698ee5999a6" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"e3c30b5a6337">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"cbce9c0a-2b75-4d9a-920f-132e14c369b9">
<td data-local-id=3D"db112388-5621-45ab-a098-9891912901ab" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7254de61cc13"><strong>Above Threshold</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a035a787-7b4e-43fc-b709-ec5ff845e68b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d496484b6830">Boolean</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f31b6e1a-3d78-4009-a657-471bd853fb7a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fc55f6de2f34">Always <code>false</code> on this port. Indica=
tes that the occupancy was below the threshold.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"8847197c286f"><strong>Tip:</strong> You do not need to use t=
he output value itself. The power of this component is in the branching =E2=
=80=94 simply connect different workflow steps to each output port to defin=
e what happens in each scenario.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"8feaef15-ea14-4154-96fb-0a81f1e967f5">
<h2 local-id=3D"da836b2300f9" id=3D"CheckOccupancy-HowItWorks">How It Works=
</h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"7c5a7344-fb01-4b92-97c7-f903072ee08f">
<li local-id=3D"ec2e4a01-e99d-48a9-ad23-2a6b5127c014">
<p local-id=3D"8356d4d25e8d">The component receives the target date, thresh=
old, and optional service filter from the previous step in the workflow (or=
 from manually configured values).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"49b8d9f6-eb5d-4942-8a30-661e92768928">
<p local-id=3D"d5c5771f4a5b">It identifies all <strong>occupiable spaces</s=
trong> (rooms, beds, etc.) in your property that belong to the selected boo=
kable services. If no services are selected, all bookable services are cons=
idered.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"278530f3-77e9-41f7-a5ff-3ac993794daa">
<p local-id=3D"aa96468957c8">It counts the <strong>occupied spaces</strong>=
 for the specified date. A space is considered occupied if it has an active=
 reservation or a resource block overlapping the target date. Canceled and =
already processed reservations are excluded.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b2da93df-05e9-4a26-bad9-ea73d6938845">
<p local-id=3D"88db76664851">The occupancy percentage is calculated as: <co=
de>(occupied spaces / total occupiable spaces) =C3=97 100</code>, rounded t=
o two decimal places. If there are no occupiable spaces, the occupancy is <=
code>0%</code>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f18860b8-4cfa-425e-9650-fe12c36aabf0">
<p local-id=3D"c32a12453ac6">The result is compared against the threshold:<=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"cfde704c-68cd-4c94-87f5-c02559a80300">
<li local-id=3D"50793933-d3b9-4ca6-bd6b-2036648ec27b">
<p local-id=3D"ae3713e0d20e">If the occupancy is <strong>greater than or eq=
ual to</strong> the threshold =E2=86=92 the workflow continues through the =
<strong>Above Threshold</strong> port.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"802e4956-21d1-4df6-9917-f5b6fd05dea1">
<p local-id=3D"908075d6877b">If the occupancy is <strong>less than</strong>=
 the threshold =E2=86=92 the workflow continues through the <strong>Below T=
hreshold</strong> port.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"ab94a262196e"><strong>Note:</strong> The occupancy calculati=
on takes into account the full resource hierarchy. If a parent space (e.g.,=
 a room) is occupied, all its child spaces (e.g., individual beds) are also=
 considered occupied, and vice versa. This ensures the occupancy percentage=
 accurately reflects the true availability of your property.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"c83a43e8-8d0a-4312-9b24-fa0f6ff841e4">
<h2 local-id=3D"17bba1c9819a" id=3D"CheckOccupancy-ExampleUseCases">Example=
 Use Cases</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"56d10da0-576c-495b-93ab-a706dc7ee1e7">
<li local-id=3D"f5dc226b-a405-4dd6-913c-7b72f53efc76">
<p local-id=3D"d0843edae2a4"><strong>Low-occupancy promotions</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Check tomorrow's occupancy every morning. If it is below 50%, automa=
tically send a promotional offer to past guests or update rates on connecte=
d channels.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0ab13c81-d31f-4919-925f-efb781f12b1d">
<p local-id=3D"75a6d561282d"><strong>High-occupancy alerts</strong> =E2=80=
=94 When a new reservation is created, check the occupancy for the arrival =
date. If it is above 90%, notify the front desk manager to prepare for a bu=
sy day.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e5bedaed-b93b-4103-a2bd-135ef5969dfe">
<p local-id=3D"31b9232bd586"><strong>Staffing decisions</strong> =E2=80=94 =
Check occupancy for the upcoming weekend. If it is below 30%, send a notifi=
cation to the operations team suggesting reduced staffing.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9aa7b1f9-798e-48f3-8b36-0b57321a1065">
<p local-id=3D"3fa067b8ca2b"><strong>Conditional upselling</strong> =E2=80=
=94 Before sending a room upgrade offer, check if the property's occupancy =
is below a certain threshold to ensure there are enough available rooms to =
offer upgrades.</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
------=_Part_38_418786640.1777536535698--
